<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-454] TimeBasedTriggeringPolicy should use event time millis</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-454</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the TimeBasedTriggeringPolicy.java, it&apos;s using system current timestamp to compare with nextRollover time:&lt;br/&gt;
Code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; now = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis();
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (now &amp;gt; nextRollover) { ... ....
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I think, it should use the event time millis: &lt;br/&gt;
Code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; now = event.getMillis();
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (now &amp;gt; nextRollover) {... ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According the event time millis,  it can be System.currentTimeMillis or Message&apos;s timestamp if the message implements TimestampMessage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think the  event.getMillis() would be the best choice for comparing with nextRollover time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
